Citation.sAbstract: In this work, in ternary mixed-electrolyte system (NaCl CdCl2 H2O), the mean activity coefficients of NaCl were measured with the potential difference method of the cell: Na ion-selective electroed (ISE)|NaCl(m1), CdCl2(m2)|Cl ion-selective electroed (ISE) at 298.15 K. Also, we chose the total ionic strength I range from 0.0100 to 1.0000 mol*kg 1 for different ionic strength fractions yb of CdCl2 with yb = (0.8, 0.6, 0.4, 0.2, 0). The experimental results gave that the mean activity coefficients of NaCl can be interpreted well by the Pitzer models, Na-ISE and Cl-ISE had a good Nernst response. Furthermore, the mixing Pitzer ion interaction parameters of Na,Cd and Na,Cd,Cl were fitted from Pitzer s equation, and the two parameters were applied to compute the values of the mean activity coefficients of CdCl2.
Citation.sTitle: Mean Activity Coefficients of NaCl in NaCl CdCl2 H2O Ternary System at 298.15 K by Potential Difference Method
